## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of sources and the scope of perspectives covered. The analysis primarily focuses on the legal and ethical dimensions of the right to strike, with less emphasis on economic analyses or case studies of specific strikes. Additionally, the report does not cover the full spectrum of international labor laws and practices, which can vary significantly across different jurisdictions.